'''Percy Reginald Lawrence-Grant''' (30 October 1870, [[Bournemouth]], [[Hampshire]], [[England]], UK &ndash; 19 February 1952, [[Santa Barbara, California|Santa Barbara]], [[California]], USA) was an [[England|English]] [[actor]] known for his supporting roles in films such as ''[[The Living Ghost]]'', ''I'll Tell the World'', ''[[Shanghai Express (film)|Shanghai Express]]'', ''[[The Mask of Fu Manchu]]'' and ''[[Son of Frankenstein]]''. He was host of the [[4th Academy Awards]] ceremonies in 1931.

